http://www.thehindu.com/news/cities/Kochi/Book-fair-begins-today/article14026557.ece

The 32nd Darshana Book Fair will get under way on Friday evening, organisers have said. Nearly 150 publishers will participate in the 10-day fair.In addition to showcasing the latest in the publishing industry, meeting of young writers, book reading by authors, literary seminars, cultural programmes by children, poetry meet, and philatelic and numismatic exhibition have also been organised as part of the exhibition.Entry for school and college students will be free. The exhibition is scheduled to conclude on February 7.